# Stateless parsers and loaders

Parsers and loaders take input as method arguments and return domain objects.
Keep them stateless or with a minimal constructor so the instance is reusable
(e.g. for different files). Inject only real dependencies in the constructor
when you have them — none yet is fine.

```ruby
# BAD: stateful loader that reads from an instance path
class ConfigLoader
  def initialize(path)
    @path = path
  end

  def load
    YAML.load_file(@path)
  end
end

# GOOD: stateless parser, input via method arg
class ConfigParser
  def parse(dev_yml_path)
    yaml = YAML.load_file(dev_yml_path)
    Config.new(name: yaml["name"], commands: yaml["commands"])
  end
end
```
